        <h2 align="center">PRIVECY & POLICIES</h2>
        <p class="indentp">His privacy policy ("Privacy Policy") applies solely to information collected by Just3click and its affiliated companies and Site developers (collectively, "Just3Click", "we", "us", "our") through the web site located at Just3Click.com, the Just3Click mobile application (as it becomes available for download) ("Mobile Application"), and their respective contents, whether accessed via computer, mobile device, telephone, or other technology (collectively, the "Site").</p>
        <p class="indentp">This Privacy Policy explains what information may be collected through the site, how such information could also be used and/or shared with others, how we safeguard it and how you'll access and control its use in reference to our marketing communications and activities. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully, because by using the site you're acknowledging that you simply understand and agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. additionally , please review our Terms and Condition www.Just3Click.com, which governs your use of the location , the Services provided via the site, and any content and knowledge you submit to the site. Any capitalized terms not defined herein are defined within the Terms and Conditions.</p>
        <h2 align="center">INFORMATION WE COLLECT</h2>
        <p class="indentp">If you book a Service Order, and you select to make a user account ("Account") you'll provide information that would reasonably be wont to contact you or to spot you personally (such as your name, e-mail address, phone number , mobile number, home address, and links to your social identities/networks, Account username and password, and mastercard number (collectively, "Personal Information")). additionally , a full history of your purchased Service Order(s) and warranty information is securely stored and accessible for future reference online through your Account. additionally , you'll provide additional information in reference to the approval of an Estimate for a Service Order, such information are going to be combined with and stored together with your Account information.</p>
        <p class="indentp">The Site can also ask you to provide other information like a description of your particular service need and photos of the matter area (e.g., your plumbing problem, your Heating, ventilation, and air conditioning issue, etc.). This information, including your Personal Information, could also be shared with the Service Professional which will be providing you with the service(s) booked by the site.</p>
        <p class="indentp"><b>If you are doing not want your Personal Information collected and used, please don't create an Account or book a Service Order</b></p>
        <h2 align="center">Information We Collect Automatically</h2>
        <p class="indentp">Whenever you visit or interact with the Site, Just3Click may use a variety of technologies that automatically or passively collect information about how the Site is accessed and used ("Usage Information"). Usage Information may include, in part, browser type, operating system, the page served, the time, the preceding and following page views, and your location. This statistical data provides us with information about the use of the Site, such as how many visitors visit a specific page on the Site, how long they stay on that page, and which hyperlinks, if any, they "click" on. This information helps us keep our website fresh and interesting to our visitors and tailor content to a visitor's interests. Usage Information is generally non-identifying, but if Just3Click associates it with you as a specific and identifiable person, Just3Click treats it as Personal Information.</p>
        <p class="indentp">Just3Click may also automatically collect your IP address or other unique identifier (" Device Identifier") for the computer, mobile device, technology or other device (collectively, "Device") you use to access the Site. A Device Identifier is a number that is automatically assigned to your Device when you access a web site or its servers, and our computers identify your Device by its Device Identifier.</p>
